The paper deals with capacity analysis of a communication channel with partial message side-information and feedback, which are topics related to information theory (cs.IT) and networking (cs.NI). The use of feedback codes and the impact of side-information on capacity also relate to signal processing (cs.SI) and multimedia (cs.MM). Additionally, the study of capacity in the presence of side-information involves the analysis of probabilistic models, which is a topic in data structures (cs.DS).
